The [[Duquesne Dukes]] play varsity men's and women's [[basketball]], [[baseball]], men's and women's [[cross country running|cross country]], men's [[golf]], men's and women's [[soccer]], men's and women's [[Swimming (sport)|swimming]], men's and women's [[tennis]], men's and women's outdoor [[Track and field|track and field]], women's indoor track and field, women's [[lacrosse]], women's [[rowing (sport)|rowing]], and women's [[volleyball]] at the [[National Collegiate Athletic Association]] [[Division I (NCAA)|Division I]] level and in the [[Atlantic Ten Conference|Atlantic 10 Conference]].<ref>{{cite web | title =Sports Finder | publisher =Duquesne University Athletics | url =http://goduquesne.cstv.com/s-finder/duqu-s-finder.html | accessdate =2007-10-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title =NCAA Compliance | publisher =Duquesne University Athletics | url =http://goduquesne.cstv.com/school-bio/duqu-school-bio-compliance.html | accessdate =2007-10-16}}</ref> In 2008, the Dukes began playing varsity football in the [[NCAA]] Division I [[Northeast Conference]]. In recent years, Duquesne football was a member of the [[NCAA]] Division I [[Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference]].<ref name="goduquesne.cstv.com">{{cite web | title =Duquesne University Football History | publisher =Duquesne University Athletics | url =http://goduquesne.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/spec-rel/091402aaa.html | accessdate =2007-10-16}}</ref> [[Collegiate wrestling|Wrestling]] is offered at Duquesne as an Independent [[NCAA]] Division I sport. Duquesne has an ACHA Division I ice hockey program.
